
<% priority 10 %>

<% if details['vul_paths'].size >1 %>
<% name "Method Check [#{details['vul_paths'].size} urls]" %>
<% else %>
<% name "Method Check [1 url]" %>
<% end %>
<b>Description:</b> Some HTTP methods are designed to aid developers in deploying and testing HTTP applications. These HTTP methods can be used for nefarious purposes if the web server is misconfigured.<br/>

<% if details.has_key?('vul_paths') then %>
			<b>Affected URLs:</b><br/>

			<% details['vul_paths'].each_pair {|path, method| %>
				<%= "#{method}" %> enabled on <%= "#{path}<br/>" %>
			<% } %>
<% end %>


<b>Advice: </b> Disable the HTTP methods that are listed.<br/>
<b>References:</b><br/>
OWASP - https://www.owasp.org/index.php/Testing_for_HTTP_Methods_and_XST_(OWASP-CM-008)<br/>
Apache - http://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.2/mod/core.html#limitexcept<br/>
Nginx - http://nginx.org/en/docs/http/ngx_http_core_module.html#limit_except<br/>
